==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Allanite
<hw>Al"lan*ite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From T.
<ets>Allan</ets>, who first distinguished it as a species.]</ety>
<fld>(min.)</fld> <def>A silicate containing a large amount of cerium.
It is usually black in color, opaque, and is related to epidote in form
and composition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Allantoic</ent>⟦br⟧
